    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-07-02T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-07-02T16:00:00-05:00" n="752"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d752">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">384.1115/7a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Port Said</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Remillard</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-07-02T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 2, 1935—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Legation at Addis Ababa is making tentative arrangements for evacuation to Port
                    Said of 10 indigent American negro citizens and <pb facs="0981" n="879"
                        xml:id="pg_879"/> will consult you as to best date for their arrival to make
                    steamer connections. Department understands that you can obtain transportation
                    third class to New York on Italian line for $135 per person. Make tentative
                    reservations at this or any lower rate. In due course you will be authorized to
                    draw not exceeding $1450 covering their transportation to New York and necessary
                    expenses awaiting sailing.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
